verses.roman:
ei ta' kahiluṅ prabhura divyonmāda-bhāva
brahmāo kahite nāre yāhāra prabhāva

synonyms: ei ta'-thus; kahiluṅ—I have described; prabhura—of Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; divya-unmāda-bhāva—transcendental ecstatic emotions; brahmāo—even Lord Brahmā; kahite nāre—cannot speak; yāhāra—of which; prabhāva—the influence.
translation: Thus I have described the transcendental ecstatic emotions of Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu. Even Lord Brahmā cannot describe their influence.
